SIMPLE: piffle
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Piffle
<hw>Pif"fle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Piffled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Piffling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <def>To be sequeamish or
delicate; hence, to act or talk triflingly or ineffectively; to talk
nonsense or about trivial matters; to twaddle; piddle.</def>
<mark>[Dial. or Slang]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> chatter, palaver, prate, tittle-tattle, twaddle,
clack, maunder, prattle, gibber, tattle, blabber, gabble.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To act in a trivial or ineffective way.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Piffle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Piffle
<hw>Pif"fle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Act of piffling; trifling talk or
action; piddling; twaddle.</def> <mark>[Dial. or Slang]</mark>
⟦ldquo⟧Futile <xex>piffle</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Kipling</au>.⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pig</ent>⟦br⟧
